# FusionSolar Weekly Report — schedule and manual triggers
#
# The container runs its own cron internally. You do NOT need a host crontab.
# Schedule is controlled entirely by the CRON_SCHEDULE env var in .env.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default schedule
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Every Friday at 8:00 AM (container time):
#   CRON_SCHEDULE=0 8 * * 5
#
# Other examples:
#   0 8 * * 1        # Every Monday at 8 AM
#   0 8 * * 1,5      # Mondays AND Fridays at 8 AM
#   0 8 1 * *        # 1st of every month at 8 AM
#   */5 * * * *      # Every 5 minutes (debug / firehose only)
#
# After changing CRON_SCHEDULE in .env:
#   docker compose up -d --force-recreate
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Send a report RIGHT NOW (one-off, doesn't touch the running container)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#   docker compose run --rm fusionsolar-extractor python /app/extract_and_email.py
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Send on next container start (e.g. after a rebuild)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Set in .env:
#   RUN_ON_START=true
# Then:
#   docker compose up -d --force-recreate
# Remember to set RUN_ON_START=false afterwards or every restart will email.
